kalma chowk flyover is a flyover and a road bridge passing over the main square of lahore. it is passing through the kalma chowk. this flyover was made due to the heavy traffic on the ferozepur road. the project was started by the punjab government on march 5, 2011 and completed in a record period, in 135 days. project's cost was rs. 2 billion. chief minister of the punjab, shahbaz sharif inaugurated it on august 14, 2011 (on independence day).